OL,3,CBride-to-be suffers serious injuries
OL,4,Cafter explosion in Paris nightclub
OL,6,FAccording to Le Parisien, the manager
OL,7,Fof the establishment, Phillipe Fatien,
OL,8,Fconfirmed there were 140 people
OL,9,Fpresent at the time of the incident.
OL,11,FIn a statement, they said: "The
OL,12,Fincident left three people injured on
OL,13,Fthe ground floor. One seriously
OL,14,Finjured person was taken care of by
OL,15,Femergency services and two others
OL,16,Finjured were treated at the scene."
OL,18,FThe nightclub closed at around 2.50am
OL,19,Fon Sunday, July 7 and then reopened
OL,20,Fthe following weekend.
